to talk to you, Naruto.

141
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:35,806
-Yeah, like I'd ever trust
what you have to say.

142
00:08:39,106 --> 00:08:40,506
NARUTO (VOICEOVER):
When going up

143
00:08:40,540 --> 00:08:45,140
against the Sharingan, if
it's one on one always run.

144
00:08:45,173 --> 00:08:49,273
If it's two on one,
attack from behind.

145
00:08:49,306 --> 00:08:52,206
This guy can cast a Genjutsu
with the same finger

146
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:55,406
he uses to make signs.

147
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,673
I've got to be careful.

148
00:08:57,706 --> 00:09:01,006
-I know that you're out
here all by yourself.

149
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,373
So why aren't you running?

150
00:09:02,406 --> 00:09:05,973
-Whatever, I can be any
number from 1 to 1,000.

151
00:09:06,006 --> 00:09:08,873
Besides, why would
I want to run?

152
00:09:08,906 --> 00:09:12,073
If I capture you then
I'll get to see Sasuke.

153
00:09:18,206 --> 00:09:20,706
-Why are you so obsessed
with my brother?

154
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:21,873
He's just a Rogue Ninja.

155
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:28,612
-It's true that we
may not be blood,

156
00:09:28,645 --> 00:09:33,045
but he's more of a brother to
me than you ever were to him.

157
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:52,245
SASUKE (VOICEOVER): You're
already under my Genjutsu.

158
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,779
[grunting]

159
00:09:59,779 --> 00:10:04,179
SASUKE (VOICEOVER): I'll say
it again, I just want to talk.

160
00:10:06,712 --> 00:10:10,579
-So are you absolutely
certain the Akatsuki leader

161
00:10:10,612 --> 00:10:12,412
is in the Hidden Rain Village?

162
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:13,679
-Yeah.

163
00:10:13,712 --> 00:10:16,345
-That place conducts very
thorough checks of anyone

164
00:10:16,379 --> 00:10:18,579
entering and exiting
their territory.

165
00:10:18,612 --> 00:10:21,445
And even keeps track
of how long they stay.

166
00:10:21,479 --> 00:10:23,112
Just preparing for
the joint chunin

167
00:10:23,145 --> 00:10:25,645
exams is difficult each
year because that village

168
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:28,345
is so strict and insular.

169
00:10:28,379 --> 00:10:29,912
Why would he pick that place?

170
00:10:29,945 --> 00:10:32,245
It just doesn't seem like
somewhere he could move around

171
00:10:32,279 --> 00:10:33,245
very freely.

172
00:10:33,279 --> 00:10:34,545
-That's true.

173
00:10:34,579 --> 00:10:37,445
But that very insular
nature makes it ideal.

174
00:10:37,479 --> 00:10:39,445
They're able to keep other
nations from learning

175
00:10:39,479 --> 00:10:41,479
about their internal
affairs and cover up

176
00:10:41,512 --> 00:10:43,945
the shame of what's going on.

177
00:10:43,979 --> 00:10:45,712
-Shame?

178
00:10:45,745 --> 00:10:48,245
-Apparently a civil war
has been raging there

179
00:10:48,279 --> 00:10:52,545
for quite some time now and
has divided the village in two.

180
00:10:52,579 --> 00:10:54,912
Word has it that the
leader of one of the sides

181
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:58,679
is the very Akatsuki leader
that we're talking about.

182
00:10:58,712 --> 00:11:01,479
-That tormented
land, it's surrounded

183
00:11:01,512 --> 00:11:04,345
by the three great nations
of Earth, Wind, and Fire.

184
00:11:04,379 --> 00:11:07,145
It has often and long
been used as the staging

185
00:11:07,179 --> 00:11:10,045
ground for all their battles.

186
00:11:10,079 --> 00:11:12,379
There's never been
domestic stability there.

187
00:11:12,412 --> 00:11:15,212
And the number of fleeing
refugees keeps rising.

188
00:11:15,245 --> 00:11:16,479
-Yes, that's right.

189
00:11:16,512 --> 00:11:19,679
And that's exactly why I
must infiltrate it and verify

190
00:11:19,712 --> 00:11:21,545
the information I've gathered.

191
00:11:21,579 --> 00:11:24,245
When I return, we'll
plan our strategy.

192
00:11:24,279 --> 00:11:26,245
-It's too dangerous to go alone.

193
00:11:26,279 --> 00:11:28,779
-I'm one of the Leaf's
legendary Sannin.

194
00:11:28,812 --> 00:11:30,979
You know what that means
just as well as I do.

195
00:11:35,912 --> 00:11:38,212
-I'm sorry, you
always seem to get

196
00:11:38,245 --> 00:11:41,479
such unfortunate assignments.

197
00:11:41,512 --> 00:11:43,345
[laughter]

198
00:11:43,379 --> 00:11:45,279
-What's with the
sudden confession?

199
00:11:45,312 --> 00:11:47,412
-I'm merely saying that
you were originally

200
00:11:47,445 --> 00:11:49,612
supposed to become Hokage.

201
00:11:49,645 --> 00:11:52,079
After all, the
third Hokage always

202
00:11:52,112 --> 00:11:53,679
wanted you to succeed him.

203
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:55,945
-I'm not cut out for
that sort of thing.

204
00:11:55,979 --> 00:11:57,912
I like being free
and unfettered.

205
00:11:57,945 --> 00:12:01,345
-You regretted not being
able to stop Orochimaru.

206
00:12:01,379 --> 00:12:03,579
That's why you tracked
his movements by yourself

207
00:12:03,612 --> 00:12:05,212
for so long, isn't it?

208
00:12:09,245 --> 00:12:12,179
-Well, I no longer
need to do that, do I?

209
00:12:12,212 --> 00:12:15,045
That also means I get to
release the sequel to my novel

210
00:12:15,079 --> 00:12:16,579
even sooner.

211
00:12:16,612 --> 00:12:20,179
-Sometimes truth is stranger
than fiction, isn't it?

212
00:12:20,212 --> 00:12:22,412
I never imagined
Orochimaru would die.

213
00:12:28,112 --> 00:12:29,445
Remember how the
three of us, we'd

214
00:12:29,479 --> 00:12:31,745
go up against the third Hokage?

215
00:12:31,779 --> 00:12:34,545
-And now, flat-as-a-board
Tsunade has become

216
00:12:34,579 --> 00:12:35,912
the big-bosomed Hokage.

217
